definition.value: ABO phenotype AB, corresponding to the genotype AB.
ABO phenotype O, corresponding to the genotype OO.
Quantification of lipopolysaccharide activity in serum.

Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of treatment with tolvaptan, an aquaretic drug that functions as a selective, competitive vasopressin receptor 2 (V2) antagonist.
Quantification of some aspect of the consumption of dietary nutritional supplements.
Quantification of some aspect of the consumption of mastiha, a natural nutritional supplement known to possess antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties.
Quantification of the expression of a gene in a cell, tissue or sample.

label.value: tumor necrosis factor alpha gene expression measurement

definition.value: Quantification of the expression of the TNFA gene, which encodes tumor necrosis factor-alpha.
Quantification of the expression of IL-6 gene, encoding interleukin-6.
Quantification of glutathione peroxidase in a sample.
The result of a measurement of circulating human polyomavirus 6-specific antibodies.
Quantification of one or more antibodies to the WU polyomavirus, typically in serum.
Quantification of one or more antibodies to the human polyomavirus 6, typically in serum.

Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulant such as used in the treatment of ADHD.
Quantification of some aspect of stimulant use, for instance in the treatment of ADHD.
Quantification of the change in cardiac troponin I in an individual over time, typically measured in blood.
Any injury to the Achilles tendon, including bursitis, tendinitis, rupture or degeneration.
Quantification of glucocorticoid receptor gene expression.

Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a recombinant tissue-plasminogen activator stimulus, a type of systemic thrombolytic agent.
Quantification of time an individual spends outside.
Quantification of some aspect of the use of insulin.
A reported family history of prostate cancer in one or more family members.
Number of times bowels opened per day.
An interval measured from the onset of the P wave in one PQRST wave complex to the onset of the P wave in the following PQRST wave complex.
Procedure to remove the appendix.

A narrow or occludable angle is when the angle of the eye is narrow or closed by the iris. Occludable anterior chamber angle is considered as a primary risk factor for primary angle closure glaucoma (PACG).
Quantification of the ratio between absolute lymphocyte count and absolute monocyte count.

Quantification of the rate at which small molecules cross the peritoneal membrane typically measured as the ratio of the concentration of creatinine in the dialysate at 4 hours of a dwell of dialysate solution to that in the plasma (4-hr D/P creatinine).
Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a peritoneal dialysis.
Quantification of the amount of complement factor H-related protein 4 in a sample.
Quantification of complement factor H-like 1 protein in a sample.

Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a cosmetic product stimulus.
Quantification of some aspect of skin roughness such as frequency or severity.
The decay of any primary tooth, in which it becomes softened, discolored, and/or porous.
The decay of any permanent tooth, in which it becomes softened, discolored, and/or porous.

value.value: An assay that allows for visualization and quantification of proteins or associated antibodies used for evaluating in situ protein spatial distribution.

A spatial discovery system where whole-slide staining of tissues using pre-designed or custom antibody panels are imaged through automated fluidics (PhenoCycler) and high-speed image acquisition (PhenoImager).

An automated fluidics system that uses oligonucleotide conjugated antibodies for tissue staining, followed by iterative cycles of applying fluorophore-conjugated reporter oligonucletides and gentle washing to generate multiplexed imaging data.
A BD Biosciences-based technology that sequences mRNA from the 3' end in an unbiased manner.
A BD Biosciences-based technology that utilizes multiplex PCR to sequence mRNA from the 3' end of specific genes from a predetermined panel.
A method that uses DNA-tagged antibodies to quantify proteins in single cells.
A spatial transcriptomics assay that involves physically expanding specimens with polymer- and hydrogel-based systems followed by in situ sequencing.

A spatial transcriptomics assay that involves physically expanding specimens with polymer- and hydrogel-based systems followed by targeted padlock probe hybridization, amplification, and in situ sequencing of padlock barcode.

A spatial transcriptomics assay that involves physically expanding specimens with polymer- and hydrogel-based systems followed by reverse transcription, amplification, and in situ sequencing of untargeted RNA using FISSEQ.
A surgical technique used by medical professionals to extract mature eggs directly from an ovary with the guidance of ultrasound imaging.

A droplet-based microfluidic library construction platform based on inDrop that incorporates dual-indexing to detect index-hopping and standard Illumina sequencing primers for high-throughput sequencing.
A microwell-based technology developed by Singleron to prepare mRNA from single cells or single nuclei and generate a next generation sequencing (NGS) library for high-throughput sequencing.
The library preparation step of a spatial transcriptomics assay.
A saliva collection method where a solution such as a saline solution or other solution is used to rinse the mouth before collection of saliva.

The collective capabilities of CITE-seq and Cell Hashing adapted for compatibility with the 5P / V(D)J single cell kit from 10x Genomics, to allow researchers to perform sample multiplexing, doublet detection and protein detection together with 5’ gene expression and V(D)J reconstruction.

Through the addition of a custom RT primer and additional PCR reactions on the low molecular weight cDNA fraction, sgRNA capture and single cell CRISPR screens with multimodal readout are made possible.
